    <td><h3>Peace Rally Says No to Bullying</h3>
    <p>Lockhart School in St. Thomas has been involved with PACER’s Unity Day and other bullying prevention efforts over the past few years. This April, they held a Peace Rally to create kindness and prevent bullying in their school. During the week they had an amazing time with skits, poetry, music and dance, all while emphasizing respect, tolerance and kindness. Joanne Saunders, a teacher at Lockhart Elementary who planned the rally, says, “We truly believe in our mission to help all students learn to get along, be respectful and considerate of each, and stop bullying.” Read more about how Lockhart School says no to bullying and yes to peace <a href="https://www.niot.org/blog/lockhart-school-st-thomas-how-we-say-no-violence-and-yes-fun-and-peace" target="_blank">here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a></p>
